nodes.name: Strictly Incompetent Bedroom
nodes.description:
'Well, I'm not sure about Kansas,' said Oz, 'for I haven't the faintest notion which way it lies. But the first thing to do is to cross the desert, and then it should be easy to find your way home.' 'How can I cross the desert?' she inquired. 'Well, I'll tell you what I think,' said the little man. 'You see, when I came to this country it was in a balloon. You also came through the air, being carried by a cyclone. So I believe the best way to get across the desert will be through the air. Now, it is quite beyond my powers to make a cyclone; but I've been thinking the matter over, and I believe I can make a balloon.' 'How?' asked Dorothy. 'A balloon,' said Oz, 'is made of silk, which is coated with glue to keep the gas in it.
